~ level1_opening

—: They told me prison changes a person.
—: What they meant was — it erases one.
—: I didn't steal anything. Didn't hurt anyone.
—: But the warden needed a closed case… and my name fit the paperwork.
—: Three rules survive in here: Stay quiet. Stay patient. Stay invisible.
—: The lock isn't my enemy. The guards are. Watch their rhythm. Every man has one.
...: Guard footsteps pass in the corridor.
—: Blink. Turn. Breathe. That's when you move.
=> END

~ level1_scrawled_note

Note: Keys don't grow on trees. Maintenance corridor. — K
—: Someone carved this deep. Not panic — intention.
—: Either someone escaped… or someone wants me to.
=> END

~ level1_stealth_tutorial

Guard: Shift report's late again. I swear this block never sleeps.
Second Guard: Last guy who ran made it two halls before bleeding out.
...: Laughter fades down the hall.
—: Good. Let them believe escape is impossible. Confidence makes people blind.
—: One mistake and they drag you back. No hearing. No record. You just… disappear into paperwork.
—: Last month wasn't me. This month is.
=> END

~ level1_first_key

...: Metal clink.
—: A key. Small thing. Heavy promise.
—: Funny how freedom fits in a pocket.
—: Who leaves this where guards never look? A ghost? An ally? Or bait.
...: Silence.
—: Doesn't matter. A cage is already a trap.
=> END

~ level1_rival

Gang Member: Hey. New fish. You walking lost… or looking for trouble?
You: I'm looking for an exit.
Gang Member: Everyone is. Difference is — we learned to stop dreaming.
—: Noise brings guards. Guards bring chains. This ends fast… or not at all.
You: I don't want enemies. Just distance.
—: Every second here costs something. Time. Blood. Witnesses.
=> END

~ level1_puzzle

...: Mechanical hum nearby.
—: Prisons aren't built to hold people. They're built to control movement.
—: Maintenance doors. Service routes. Forgotten passages.
—: The guards walk the same paths every day. They stopped seeing them. I didn't.
PA System: All units remain at assigned posts. Unauthorized movement detected in Block C.
—: Block C is me. Good. Let them chase shadows while I become one.
=> END

~ level1_exit

...: A large reinforced door blocks the way forward.
—: There it is. Not freedom. Just a deeper layer of the lie.
—: Tourists never see what's past this door. Only guards… and prisoners meant to stay forgotten.
...: An alarm begins, faint and distant.
Guard: Perimeter check! Move!
—: Heart steady. Hands steady. One key. One chance. Don't look back.
=> END

~ level1_transition

...: The door unlocks. Heavy metal groans open.
...: Cold air replaces rot. Oil replaces sweat. The prison changes its smell… like stepping inside its lungs.
—: Cell block cleared. Now I'm inside the machine that keeps this place alive. Boilers. Pipes. Power lines.
—: No conversations here. Only watchers.
—: I'm still trapped. But tonight the warden sleeps knowing everything is under control. He's wrong.
Radio: Block C is clear. If you're listening… avoid the blue uniforms on the upper catwalk.
—: Blue uniforms? Not guards. Something else. Whoever you are… keep talking.
=> END

~ level2_opening

...: Steam vents hiss in the dark.
—: No windows. No clocks. Just heat and shadows. Perfect place to bury mistakes.
—: Guards here don't patrol. They hunt.
—: Cross the floor unseen. Find their access route. Turn their system against them.
—: They took my name. They took my years. They wrote my guilt in permanent ink. Now I write my way out.
—: Escape first. Truth second. Revenge… if there's time.
=> END

~ level2_float_first

...: The air changes — lighter, pulled in two directions at once.
—: Steam columns. Updrafts and downdrafts fighting each other.
—: Don't fight the current. Ride it.
=> END

~ level2_float_rise

...: Warm air pushes from below.
—: Up. Slow. Deliberate. Like the building is exhaling.
—: Guards below can't track what they can't predict.
=> END

~ level2_float_descend

...: Cold draft pulls downward.
—: Down is faster than up. Gravity still wins in here — it just takes its time.
—: Soft landing. No sound. No proof I passed through.
=> END

~ level2_float_deep

...: Deeper into the works. Pipes scream when the boilers breathe.
—: One wrong drift and I become another accident report.
—: Steady. Small movements. Let the steam hide the rest.
=> END

~ hook_k

K: You're not the first innocent they locked away. Just the first who listened.
=> END

~ hook_warden

Warden: Order requires sacrifice. You should feel honored.
=> END

~ hook_rival

Rival Inmate: I'll show you the tunnel. You make the distraction. Fair trade.
=> END

~ hook_radio

Unknown Radio Voice: The prison isn't just a prison. Keep digging.
=> END

~ level2_level3_transition

...: Signs give up pretending this is rehab. Wiring runs toward the perimeter like veins toward a bruise.
—: Air thins past the boilers — metal cold, ozone and rain just out of sight.
—: One door still claims "EXIT." Tonight I prove whether it lied.
=> END

~ level3_opening

—: Upper works. Blinking floods through grime. Enough roof to pretend the sky is close.
—: If alarms love me, they'll sing in every corridor. Quiet means they already won.
=> END

~ game_victory

...: Seal breaks. Weather hits sharp — honest cold, wet night, breathing room.
PA System (fading): All sectors secure. Contain perimeter—
—: They'll cut the feeds, shred the tapes, bury my name deeper than the bunk I left.
Friendly Radio Voice: You're past our lines. Doesn't matter what they print on paper. You're gone now.
—: They sold me guilt in permanent ink. I walked out owning the only copy that proves me human.
—: No badge. No cell. Finish line is just darkness I chose for myself.
=> END
